news.title: SC dismisses Zostel's appeal against Oyo
news.para: A bench comprising Justice Sanjay Kumar and Justice Satish Chandra Sharma dismissed Zostel’s special leave petition against the High Court order. The dispute traces back to 2015, when Oyo considered acquiring Zostel’s business including Zo Rooms.

news.title: Gujarat government proposes merger of five towns into Ahmedabad civic body limits
news.para: Ahmedabad is poised for significant expansion as the state government considers merging five surrounding municipalities—Sanand, Mehemdabad, Bareja, Kalol, and Dahegam—into the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC). This strategic move aims to enhance coordinated urban development and improve infrastructure in rapidly growing areas before the 2026 municipal elections.

news.title: Gurgaon administration proposes steep hike in circle rates
news.para: Gurgaon residents brace for potential property price hikes as the district administration proposes significant increases in circle rates, ranging from 8% to 77% for residential areas and up to 145% for agricultural land. Upscale areas like DLF I-V could see a 10-20% rise.

news.title: SC wants early high court hearing on Haryana’s S+4 policy
news.para: The Supreme Court addressed a petition challenging Haryana's stilt+4 construction policy, directing the Punjab and Haryana High Court to consider interim relief requests. The petition raises concerns about the policy's impact on Gurgaon's infrastructure. The petitioner seeks a stay on new approvals and an oversight committee, highlighting the urgency of addressing urban expansion issues.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 1% stamp duty relief to women buyers on properties up to Rs 1 crore
news.para: In Uttar Pradesh, women buying properties up to Rs 1 crore now benefit from a 1% stamp duty waiver, effective July 29. This revision, increasing the previous limit from Rs 10 lakh, aims to encourage female property ownership and financial inclusion. While benefiting mid-segment buyers, some feel the cap should be higher, especially in Noida.

news.title: About 10-50% hike in collector rates on cards in Panchkula
news.para: Panchkula is considering a significant hike in collector rates. The proposed increase ranges from 10% to 50% for the fiscal year 2025-2026. Residential and industrial properties could see the biggest jump. Sectors 4, 5, 6 (MDC), and 6-11 may face a 50% rise. Public objections are welcome until July 31. Monica Gupta encourages residents to submit their concerns.

news.title: Prayagraj development body to hold lottery system for flat allotment on August 5
news.para: The Prayagraj Development Authority (PDA) will conduct a transparent lottery on August 5 at 11:30 am to allocate flats across 12 residential schemes. Online applications were accepted from June 25 to July 15, with 154 eligible applicants registered.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body allocates affordable housing to slum-dwellers in lottery
news.para: The Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA) conducted a lottery, allocating houses to 38 beneficiaries under its Affordable Housing Projects (AHP) and In-situ Slum Redevelopment (ISSR) schemes. Beneficiaries received houses in Subudhipur, Santi Nagar, and Chandrasekharpur, marking a significant step in BDA's efforts to improve living conditions for the urban poor by providing access to essential infrastructure.

news.title: Telangana RERA orders developer to refund buyers for failing to deliver project on time
news.para: Telangana Real Estate Regulatory Authority instructed Jayathri Infrastructure to refund buyers. This order includes the principal amount and interest. The directive follows complaints about the Western Galaxy project delay. Musunuru Siva Sankara Rao and Kalvala Suman filed complaints. They cited breach of agreement and non-compliance. RERA noted over twenty similar complaints against the developer.

news.title: ED raids unearth multiple property documents linked to former Vasai-Virar civic chief
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) seized property documents linked to Anil Pawar, former civic chief of Vasai-Virar City Municipal Corporation, during raids at 12 locations. Pawar allegedly laundered bribe money through shell entities created in the names of family and associates, coinciding with his tenure as VVCMC commissioner.

news.title: Can’t limit zero-period relief once state accepts delay in land handover: Allahabad HC
news.para: The Allahabad High Court has ruled in favor of Empire E-Parks, directing the Greater Noida Authority to grant a full ‘zero-period' waiver. This waiver covers interest and penal interest accrued during an 18-year construction delay. The delay was due to the company's inability to take possession of the allotted land.

news.title: Nashik: Mhada & NMC streamline issues related to land transfer for affordable housing
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation and MHADA have resolved issues concerning the transfer of developmental rights to builders. This collaboration aims to boost affordable housing projects for lower-income groups and the economically weaker sections. NMC will provide TDR for plots given to MHADA, and vice versa, facilitating the construction of affordable homes on reserved plots.

news.title: Arunachal Pradesh launches online building permit system
news.para: Arunachal Pradesh has launched an online building permission system. Balo Raja, the Urban Affairs Minister, inaugurated the digital platform. The system aims to streamline building permit issuance across the state. It promises improved efficiency and transparency. The online system will be used for all construction permits. The government emphasizes public awareness and compliance.

news.title: Haryana chief minister announces 100 sq yards plot for one lakh poor families
news.para: Haryana Chief Minister Nayab Singh Saini announced that one lakh landless 'Antyodaya' families will soon receive 100 square yard plots, with plans for another lakh beneficiaries in the next phase. Government hospitals in 10 districts will offer upgraded, affordable healthcare services starting August 15. Additionally, sunflower and mustard oil mills will be established to ensure fair prices for farmers' crops.

news.title: Keppel's net profit rises to $332.54 million in H1 2025
news.para: Keppel announced strong first-half earnings, driven by a real estate recovery and resilient infrastructure. Net profit rose to S$431 million, excluding legacy offshore assets. A S$500 million share buyback and a 15 Singapore cents dividend were declared. Funds under management reached S$91 billion, with a focus on monetizing non-core assets.

news.title: Not investigating any irregularities in Indiabulls, found no wrong: CBI tells SC
news.para: The CBI informed the Supreme Court that its investigation into Indiabulls Housing Finance Limited (now Sammaan Capital Limited) found no evidence of irregularities in loan disbursements to corporate entities. While the CBI found no wrongdoing, other agencies like the ED and SEBI have indicated potential irregularities and are further investigating the matter.

news.title: IndiQube slumps about 15% in trading debut on July 30
news.para: IndiQube Spaces' shares stumbled nearly 15% on their market debut, valuing the workspace provider at 44.13 billion rupees amidst muted markets. Despite a heavily subscribed IPO, the listing opened at a discount. Analysts cite regional revenue concentration and rising competition from players like Awfis and Smartworks as potential headwinds.

news.title: Zillow sued by CoStar Group for 'massive' copyright violations
news.para: CoStar Group has filed a lawsuit against Zillow, accusing the real estate portal of copyright infringement by publishing nearly 47,000 copyrighted photos without permission. CoStar seeks over $1 billion in damages, alleging Zillow used the photos to boost its rental listings business and generate revenue through advertising packages.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers IPO subscribed 3.59 times on day 1
news.para: Sri Lotus Developers, backed by Bollywood stars and investor Ashish Kacholia, witnessed its IPO subscribed 3.59 times on the first day. The IPO received bids for 14.23 crore equity shares against the 3.96 crore on offer. The company aims to utilize the raised capital for ongoing projects and general corporate purposes.

news.title: CBI registers 22 FIRs on SC's directions to investigate builders-banks nexus in NCR
news.para: Following Supreme Court directives, the CBI has registered 22 FIRs investigating a builder-bank nexus that allegedly cheated homebuyers in the NCR region. Searches were conducted across 47 locations in Delhi and NCR, targeting prominent builders and financial institutions. The investigation stems from a subvention scheme where developers defaulted, leaving homebuyers to repay loans for unpossessed flats.
